# Senior UI/UX Polish: Secondary Pages

This phase focuses on bringing the secondary pages (Trending, Subscriptions, History, Liked, and Shorts) up to the "Senior AI Designer" level of quality. We will standardize grids, unify design tokens (Glassmorphism), and ensure pixel-perfect consistency with the newly updated Home and Watch pages.

## Proposed Changes

### Global Design Tokens & Standardization
- **Grid Consistency**: Update all video grids to support `2xl:grid-cols-6` and `xl:grid-cols-4` (matching Home).
- **Radius Unification**: Standardize on `rounded-xl` (12-16px) for cards and `rounded-[32px]` for large containers/sections.
- **Glass System**: Replace `bg-surface` and `bg-foreground` with standard glass tokens (`bg-white/5`, `backdrop-blur-xl`, `border-white/10`).

### Page Specific Refinements

#### [MODIFY] [TrendingClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/trending/TrendingClient.tsx)
- Update grid and skeletons to match [HomeClient](file:///C:/GOLive/app/HomeClient.tsx#13-170).
- Refine header with premium "Glass" styling and consistent radii.

